       <h1 class="text-center mb-5 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s"> &#128188; Tips While Applying for Jobs</h1>

  <!-- Tip 1 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>1. Tailor Your Resume for Each Role</h5>
    <p>Don't send the same CV to every job. Adjust your resume to highlight the skills the job is asking for.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      &#10060; <em>Wrong:</em> "Proficient in various frontend frameworks."<br>
      &#9989; <em>Better:</em> "Built 3 responsive web apps using React and Tailwind CSS."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 2 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>2. Write a Clear and Concise Cover Letter</h5>
    <p>A personalized cover letter shows effort and interest in that specific company.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      &#10060; "I'm interested in the job at your company."<br>
      &#9989; "I'm excited to apply for the Marketing Associate position at GulfTalent, where I admire your data-driven approach to regional talent development."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 3 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>3. Apply Only to Relevant Jobs</h5>
    <p>Focus on roles that match your current skills and growth level.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      If you have 1 year of experience in customer service, apply for "Customer Support Representative" roles - not "Customer Service Manager."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 4 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>4. Keep Your LinkedIn Profile Updated</h5>
    <p>Make sure your LinkedIn profile matches your resume and has a clear headline.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      &#9989; "Sales Executive | 3+ Years in B2B Sales | UAE Market Experience"<br>
      &#10060; "Looking for new opportunities"</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 5 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>5. Double-Check for Errors</h5>
    <p>Proofread your documents for typos or grammar issues.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
       &#9989; "Experienced in custumer service."<br>
      &#10060; "Experienced in customer service."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 6 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>6. Follow Application Instructions</h5>
    <p>Carefully read what the job post asks for and follow it exactly.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      If the post says: "Email with subject: Job Application - Dubai Sales Executive"<br>
      Then use that exact subject, not "My Application for Sales."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 7 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>7. Be Honest</h5>
    <p>Always be truthful about your skills and experience.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      &#10060; Don't say: "Fluent in Arabic" if you only know basic phrases.<br>
       &#9989; Say: "Basic proficiency in spoken Arabic - currently improving through self-study."</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Tip 8 -->
  <div class="mb-4">
    <h5>8. Prepare for Follow-Up</h5>
    <p>Be ready to receive emails or calls. Check your spam folder too.</p>
    <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
      If you get a call and you'e busy: "Thanks for calling! May I call you back in 15 minutes so I can be in a quiet place?"</p>
  </div>
</div>


